1
00:00:00,584 --> 00:00:02,336
I didn't kill Teacher Sam.

2
00:00:02,420 --> 00:00:05,047
You have to tell me every little detail!

3
00:00:05,131 --> 00:00:07,174
Otherwise, you'll end up in jail!

4
00:00:08,509 --> 00:00:10,594
Just tell them I did it, Matteo!

5
00:00:18,436 --> 00:00:20,187
Matt pushed Teacher Sam.

6
00:00:20,271 --> 00:00:23,482
Martinez, looks like we have new
suspects in the Sam Ignacio case.

7
00:00:23,566 --> 00:00:26,026
-Jem is lying to you.
-Can we talk?

8
00:00:26,110 --> 00:00:29,613
-Matteo killed Teacher Sam!
-That's not true.

9
00:00:29,697 --> 00:00:32,032
If you're just going to insult me,
then leave!

10
00:00:32,116 --> 00:00:34,785
Go be with your murderer brother!

11
00:00:34,869 --> 00:00:36,871
He might not come home anymore!

12
00:00:36,954 --> 00:00:38,372
You liar!

13
00:00:40,249 --> 00:00:42,209
There's a small laceration on the leg.

14
00:00:42,293 --> 00:00:43,627
Is Jem's baby okay?

15
00:00:45,254 --> 00:00:47,006
Jem has confessed. She lied.

16
00:00:47,089 --> 00:00:48,424
I'll admit it now.

17
00:00:48,507 --> 00:00:51,552
I'm the one who killed Sam.
I'm the one who killed my sister.

18
00:00:51,635 --> 00:00:54,388
Today is a victory
for everyone who loved Sam.

19
00:00:54,472 --> 00:00:57,308
Her case has finally been solved

20
00:00:57,391 --> 00:00:59,685
so her soul can finally rest in peace.

21
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:08,527
You pull it so it goes higher.

22
00:01:08,611 --> 00:01:09,653
Pull it.

23
00:01:12,323 --> 00:01:13,199
There we go!

24
00:01:29,423 --> 00:01:30,591
It's a butterfly.

25
00:01:46,649 --> 00:01:50,986
Miss, why does the butterfly fly so high?

26
00:01:51,070 --> 00:01:53,906
Isn't it scared?

27
00:01:56,325 --> 00:02:00,287
I think the butterfly gets scared too.

28
00:02:06,460 --> 00:02:10,714
Even if it doesn't know where it's going?

29
00:02:10,798 --> 00:02:13,634
Well, it trusts its wings.

30
00:02:13,717 --> 00:02:17,054
It flies because
that's how it sees the world.

31
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:23,602
What if its wings get hurt?

32
00:02:23,686 --> 00:02:26,397
It'll take a break.

33
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:29,608
And when it gains its strength back,

34
00:02:29,692 --> 00:02:34,280
then, I guess it'll just try to fly again.

35
00:02:35,739 --> 00:02:40,536
So, it's brave even when it's small?

36
00:02:42,746 --> 00:02:46,500
Courage isn't measured by size.

37
00:02:46,584 --> 00:02:50,004
It's when you decide
that you're going to fly

38
00:02:50,087 --> 00:02:52,381
even though you're feeling scared.

39
00:02:52,464 --> 00:02:54,842
That's what courage is.

40
00:02:56,635 --> 00:02:59,471
You're small,
but you're very brave, right?

41
00:03:00,347 --> 00:03:01,390
Thank you.

42
00:03:03,267 --> 00:03:04,810
I love you.

43
00:03:49,188 --> 00:03:51,440
What's wrong, dear?

44
00:04:03,118 --> 00:04:06,956
How about you, Anton?
When are you going to confess?

45
00:05:34,376 --> 00:05:37,671
How about you, Anton?
When are you going to confess?

46
00:05:59,234 --> 00:06:01,361
Who are you?

47
00:06:11,163 --> 00:06:14,708
Why do you have Sam's phone?

48
00:06:19,505 --> 00:06:24,259
Why were you crying?

49
00:06:26,178 --> 00:06:29,723
Are you and Papa okay?

50
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:37,981
We're just dealing with some problems.

51
00:06:38,065 --> 00:06:43,153
But we can handle it.
Don't worry about us.

52
00:06:46,323 --> 00:06:52,621
Would you like to do something
or go somewhere?

53
00:06:54,790 --> 00:06:58,919
How about the weekend trip?

54
00:07:00,587 --> 00:07:03,132
I want to go.

55
00:07:03,215 --> 00:07:05,551
All of us.

56
00:07:08,595 --> 00:07:12,224
Okay. We'll go.

57
00:07:17,604 --> 00:07:19,398
Come here.

58
00:07:46,967 --> 00:07:50,679
It's not important who I am.
But I have Sam's phone,

59
00:07:50,762 --> 00:07:52,806
and all the secrets in it.

60
00:07:58,687 --> 00:08:01,565
What do you want from me?

61
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:07,988
You're the one
who wants something from me.

62
00:08:08,071 --> 00:08:10,908
I'll give you the phone for a price.

63
00:08:17,748 --> 00:08:20,417
How much?

64
00:08:25,589 --> 00:08:30,177
100,000 pesos. Non-negotiable.

65
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:51,198
Pa?

66
00:08:54,326 --> 00:08:56,370
Pia, what are you doing here?

67
00:08:56,453 --> 00:08:59,122
I'm trying to call my partner
for the school project.

68
00:08:59,206 --> 00:09:01,166
He won't pick up.

69
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:05,045
If he doesn't want to cooperate,
why don't you tell your teacher?

70
00:09:06,296 --> 00:09:07,589
It's okay.

71
00:09:07,673 --> 00:09:08,757
It's…

72
00:09:09,424 --> 00:09:10,884
It's my fault too.

73
00:09:11,635 --> 00:09:14,638
It slipped my mind
because of what happened.

74
00:09:29,528 --> 00:09:32,406
Hi, Kyle. This is Pia, your partner
on the science project.

75
00:09:32,489 --> 00:09:35,284
Are you free tomorrow to work on it?

76
00:09:40,455 --> 00:09:43,000
I'm free at lunchtime.

77
00:09:57,222 --> 00:09:58,932
Pa, are you okay?

78
00:10:04,062 --> 00:10:07,774
I'm okay. I'm just tired
from what happened today.

79
00:10:10,485 --> 00:10:13,071
Let's go inside. You need to rest.

80
00:10:24,916 --> 00:10:26,752
I can't hide it anymore.

81
00:10:28,170 --> 00:10:30,130
My conscience is eating me alive.

82
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:34,926
My sister keeps appearing
in my dreams every night.

83
00:10:37,220 --> 00:10:38,722
The truth is…

84
00:10:39,723 --> 00:10:42,309
she was good to me.

85
00:10:43,769 --> 00:10:46,521
She tried to help me many times.

86
00:10:47,731 --> 00:10:49,274
But until the very end,

87
00:10:50,567 --> 00:10:54,196
I never managed to do
anything right for her.

88
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:58,408
I'll admit it now.

89
00:11:00,702 --> 00:11:02,537
I'm the one who killed Sam.

90
00:11:03,705 --> 00:11:05,707
I'm the one who killed my sister.

91
00:11:12,047 --> 00:11:13,507
-I didn't want to…
-He confessed.

92
00:11:13,590 --> 00:11:15,217
Why don't you believe him?

93
00:11:17,677 --> 00:11:19,638
Not all confessions are true.

94
00:11:22,474 --> 00:11:23,934
Jackie.

95
00:11:24,017 --> 00:11:26,144
Let's put Sam to rest.

96
00:11:26,228 --> 00:11:27,771
Let's move on.

97
00:11:30,857 --> 00:11:32,651
If it was that easy…

98
00:11:34,945 --> 00:11:36,822
I would've done it a long time ago.

99
00:11:39,991 --> 00:11:43,578
The files she left behind
about Able Hearts,

100
00:11:43,662 --> 00:11:45,372
those weren't a rumor.

101
00:11:45,455 --> 00:11:46,998
Those were real.

102
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:55,549
I talked to…

103
00:11:56,299 --> 00:11:57,592
the mayor.

104
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:03,515
He offered me
Sam's position at Able Hearts.

105
00:12:07,769 --> 00:12:09,396
Are you going to accept it?

106
00:12:10,522 --> 00:12:11,565
No.

107
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:13,984
Family is my priority.

108
00:12:15,735 --> 00:12:16,862
That's right.

109
00:12:17,904 --> 00:12:19,239
Family first.

110
00:12:21,491 --> 00:12:25,495
And that includes protecting them
from bigger problems.

111
00:12:30,125 --> 00:12:32,419
If there's corruption,

112
00:12:32,502 --> 00:12:35,672
isn't it even more dangerous
to just look the other way?

113
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:39,426
I'm not reckless,
but I won't back down either

114
00:12:39,509 --> 00:12:42,345
just because it's convenient and easier.

115
00:12:42,929 --> 00:12:46,475
-But, Jackie, how far will you go?
-Until the truth comes out.

116
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:51,021
Until everything's clear for our kids.

117
00:12:51,980 --> 00:12:54,608
I won't put our family in danger.

118
00:12:54,691 --> 00:12:58,236
But I also won't let fear
dictate our choices.

119
00:13:08,288 --> 00:13:10,665
Eli wants us to go on that weekend trip.

120
00:13:14,503 --> 00:13:15,587
I'll take care of that.

121
00:13:17,005 --> 00:13:18,340
Let's do that.

122
00:13:19,174 --> 00:13:20,383
We need it.

123
00:13:23,595 --> 00:13:27,641
It's better for the kids
to see us facing things together.

124
00:13:32,938 --> 00:13:38,902
MATTEO CARPIO, MURDERER!

125
00:14:04,219 --> 00:14:05,762
They say you're smart.

126
00:14:07,138 --> 00:14:09,849
But how come you don't know
that wet tissue won't erase that?

127
00:14:12,602 --> 00:14:14,104
Wow!

128
00:14:14,187 --> 00:14:17,065
Thank you for pointing out
that I am smart.

129
00:14:19,526 --> 00:14:20,944
I noticed you earlier.

130
00:14:21,778 --> 00:14:25,240
But when I saw what you're doing,
I thought you looked stupid.

131
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:29,119
So I borrowed this from the janitor.

132
00:14:48,179 --> 00:14:49,180
Thanks.

133
00:14:51,725 --> 00:14:54,978
It's our first time
talking in person, right?

134
00:14:56,354 --> 00:14:57,606
I think so.

135
00:15:00,233 --> 00:15:03,528
What are your plans for our project?

136
00:15:07,115 --> 00:15:08,950
I have purchased the materials.

137
00:15:09,034 --> 00:15:11,202
I just need your help assembling it.

138
00:15:15,332 --> 00:15:17,584
You know, you should just ignore this.

139
00:15:18,251 --> 00:15:21,338
Someone already confessed, right?
The victim's brother.

140
00:15:21,421 --> 00:15:23,173
They should be ashamed.

141
00:15:24,799 --> 00:15:27,469
They believed in fake news.

142
00:15:45,070 --> 00:15:46,279
It's done.

143
00:15:57,999 --> 00:15:59,417
Tell him, okay?

144
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:04,506
Lauro, what's that?

145
00:16:04,589 --> 00:16:08,009
Chief, the order to transfer him
to the provincial jail is out.

146
00:16:09,719 --> 00:16:10,970
Okay, leave us for now.

147
00:16:15,058 --> 00:16:17,435
I've said everything I needed to say.

148
00:16:19,437 --> 00:16:20,689
Who is it?

149
00:16:21,481 --> 00:16:23,400
Who are you taking the fall for?

150
00:16:28,321 --> 00:16:30,323
I don't know what you're talking about.

151
00:16:34,077 --> 00:16:35,078
Lauro!

152
00:16:36,246 --> 00:16:37,122
Take him.

153
00:16:40,542 --> 00:16:41,710
Let's go.

154
00:17:15,785 --> 00:17:19,289
Sheila, I'm sorry for coming unannounced.

155
00:17:19,372 --> 00:17:22,876
No, that's okay.
I was just cleaning inside.

156
00:17:24,461 --> 00:17:26,129
I heard about Ted.

157
00:17:27,756 --> 00:17:29,883
Do you believe him?

158
00:17:31,176 --> 00:17:32,886
Ted's a jerk, but…

159
00:17:34,763 --> 00:17:37,515
I don't know what to believe.

160
00:17:38,725 --> 00:17:40,935
But if Ted said that,

161
00:17:41,019 --> 00:17:44,397
even though it's painful
for us as his family,

162
00:17:44,481 --> 00:17:46,900
we have no choice but to believe it.

163
00:17:48,526 --> 00:17:54,783
All we pray is for Sam to have peace.

164
00:17:56,951 --> 00:18:00,789
Sheila, would you mind
if I take a look at Sam's stuff?

165
00:18:21,559 --> 00:18:23,937
Let's trade tonight. Prepare the money.

166
00:18:24,020 --> 00:18:25,980
But wait for my instructions.

167
00:18:38,535 --> 00:18:39,744
Let's trade tonight. Prepare the money.

168
00:18:39,828 --> 00:18:41,371
But wait for my instructions.

169
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:52,257
The mayor's here, Chief.

170
00:18:57,053 --> 00:18:58,805
I dropped by to see you.

171
00:19:02,058 --> 00:19:04,686
I'm sure this case has kept you up
for nights on end.

172
00:19:04,769 --> 00:19:07,021
-It's part of the job.
-That's right.

173
00:19:08,189 --> 00:19:11,276
So let's not make things
harder for ourselves.

174
00:19:12,026 --> 00:19:13,403
You know, sometimes,

175
00:19:13,486 --> 00:19:18,241
some things are better left closed.

176
00:19:18,324 --> 00:19:19,868
That's right, Mayor.

177
00:19:19,951 --> 00:19:22,579
There are other things
we need to pay attention to.

178
00:19:22,662 --> 00:19:23,913
That's right.

179
00:19:24,664 --> 00:19:25,748
Okay.

180
00:20:14,088 --> 00:20:16,341
Where is Pia?

181
00:21:57,191 --> 00:21:59,694
Sam, I'm just curious.

182
00:22:01,738 --> 00:22:03,573
How does it feel

183
00:22:03,656 --> 00:22:06,534
growing up with parents who are both deaf?

184
00:22:18,588 --> 00:22:24,135
Of course, there were times
when I felt like we were different.

185
00:22:24,218 --> 00:22:26,679
Because you know, there'd always be people

186
00:22:26,763 --> 00:22:28,806
who'd badmouth us.

187
00:22:28,890 --> 00:22:30,850
They'd say that my family was abnormal.

188
00:22:33,644 --> 00:22:37,482
But my parents would always tell me

189
00:22:37,565 --> 00:22:41,360
that our being different isn't a weakness,

190
00:22:41,444 --> 00:22:43,738
it's our strength.

191
00:22:43,821 --> 00:22:46,699
We just need to learn how to use it.

192
00:22:48,409 --> 00:22:50,078
It makes sense, right?

193
00:22:52,121 --> 00:22:55,083
I hope Eli learns the same thing.

194
00:22:55,166 --> 00:22:58,294
So he can grow to be
just as confident as you are.

195
00:23:59,313 --> 00:24:00,731
You got to know each other?

196
00:24:08,489 --> 00:24:10,116
Yes.

197
00:24:10,199 --> 00:24:12,910
Your friend is funny, Pia.

198
00:24:17,915 --> 00:24:21,419
What? Why? Aren't we friends?

199
00:24:21,502 --> 00:24:23,171
We're even doing a project together.

200
00:24:26,716 --> 00:24:30,761
We told you,
don't talk to strangers, right?

201
00:24:34,015 --> 00:24:37,727
He's not a stranger. He's Kyle.

202
00:24:38,269 --> 00:24:40,563
I know that. He taught me that earlier.

203
00:24:40,646 --> 00:24:42,023
Look at me, Pia.

204
00:24:54,994 --> 00:24:56,704
Wow, you two really became close.

205
00:24:56,787 --> 00:24:59,081
He even taught you sign language.

206
00:24:59,165 --> 00:25:00,791
That's not all.

207
00:25:00,875 --> 00:25:04,253
I also asked him to teach me how to sign

208
00:25:04,879 --> 00:25:08,633
what I wanted to tell you
when we first met.

209
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:31,572
You're so naughty! You're so naughty!

210
00:25:35,826 --> 00:25:38,829
Don't scold Eli.
I just wanted to tease you.

211
00:25:40,248 --> 00:25:42,083
Whatever!

212
00:25:42,166 --> 00:25:45,920
Let's finish the project,
so Eli and I can go home early.

213
00:25:51,384 --> 00:25:52,551
I have an idea.

214
00:25:54,762 --> 00:25:57,723
What if we finish this at your house?

215
00:25:57,807 --> 00:26:01,560
So you don't have to worry
about what time you get home.

216
00:26:02,812 --> 00:26:04,313
Won't your parents look for you?

217
00:26:04,397 --> 00:26:06,190
Nope, no one's home anyway.

218
00:26:09,986 --> 00:26:12,280
Okay. I'll ask Mama.

219
00:26:15,074 --> 00:26:16,450
Ugly!

220
00:26:39,098 --> 00:26:41,851
-I don't know yet.
-Your treat, right?

221
00:26:45,021 --> 00:26:46,522
I'll lend you money.

222
00:26:53,237 --> 00:26:56,657
He's taking too long.

223
00:26:56,741 --> 00:26:59,994
You're in a hurry, right? Me too.

224
00:28:06,227 --> 00:28:09,563
What are you doing here?
You're investigating again?

225
00:28:10,189 --> 00:28:11,607
My son studies here.

226
00:28:11,690 --> 00:28:13,401
I have to take care
of something at the cashier.

227
00:28:13,484 --> 00:28:15,194
It's already closed.

228
00:28:18,739 --> 00:28:20,032
Do you mind?

229
00:28:22,785 --> 00:28:24,036
Mrs. Carpio.

230
00:28:26,497 --> 00:28:28,124
Sam Ignacio's case…

231
00:28:29,291 --> 00:28:32,002
Sam Ignacio's case isn't closed yet.

232
00:28:32,586 --> 00:28:34,338
Ted already confessed, didn't he?

233
00:28:34,422 --> 00:28:37,925
And we both know that Ted is lying.

234
00:28:38,717 --> 00:28:40,678
You said it yourself, didn't you?

235
00:28:41,470 --> 00:28:44,348
We don't have enough evidence against--

236
00:28:48,018 --> 00:28:51,230
I just said that to keep you
away from the case.

237
00:28:53,732 --> 00:28:54,984
It's too dangerous.

238
00:28:56,068 --> 00:28:57,236
He's your boss, right?

239
00:28:58,237 --> 00:29:02,158
I want to find evidence,
so I'm just playing along for now.

240
00:29:10,791 --> 00:29:13,377
Where do I stick it? Here?

241
00:29:14,128 --> 00:29:16,213
Yeah, here. Like this.

242
00:29:16,297 --> 00:29:18,591
Just flip it. That looks better.

243
00:29:22,428 --> 00:29:24,472
You know, usually…

244
00:29:24,555 --> 00:29:27,766
when Pia brings home a male classmate,

245
00:29:28,517 --> 00:29:30,269
I don't allow it.

246
00:29:30,352 --> 00:29:35,357
But I heard you made Eli smile earlier,
so you get a free pass.

247
00:29:36,066 --> 00:29:38,152
It's just, Eli's funny.

248
00:29:38,861 --> 00:29:40,946
He's very playful.

249
00:29:41,030 --> 00:29:42,531
He'd be a fun brother.

250
00:29:47,328 --> 00:29:49,497
Why? What are your siblings like?

251
00:29:51,040 --> 00:29:53,876
I don't have siblings. I'm an only child.

252
00:29:55,961 --> 00:29:58,631
Your parents, where are they?

253
00:30:01,217 --> 00:30:02,510
They're busy.

254
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:06,430
Have dinner here, Kyle.

255
00:30:09,767 --> 00:30:10,976
Is it okay?

256
00:30:11,602 --> 00:30:12,770
Of course.

257
00:30:13,771 --> 00:30:15,648
I knew there was a different voice.

258
00:30:15,731 --> 00:30:17,608
-Pa.
-You have a visitor.

259
00:30:20,361 --> 00:30:21,862
Is he Pia's suitor?

260
00:30:23,113 --> 00:30:27,701
Pa, no. He's my partner
for a school project.

261
00:30:28,452 --> 00:30:32,331
-Kyle, this is my dad.
-Good evening.

262
00:30:32,414 --> 00:30:33,999
It was just a joke, okay? Relax.

263
00:30:35,626 --> 00:30:37,962
Fortunately, he's just
your partner for a project

264
00:30:38,045 --> 00:30:41,674
because if he's your suitor,
Pia, my answer is no.

265
00:30:41,757 --> 00:30:45,261
-Pa, that's not the case.
-Let the kids be.

266
00:30:45,344 --> 00:30:47,429
Get dressed, we're about to eat.

267
00:30:47,513 --> 00:30:49,807
-Go.
-I'll just get dressed.

268
00:30:57,106 --> 00:30:59,608
Ma, our cutter is a bit dull.

269
00:31:10,286 --> 00:31:13,247
Bry, whiskey on the rocks, please.

270
00:31:30,472 --> 00:31:31,849
Are you really a hard drinker?

271
00:31:32,808 --> 00:31:34,685
Or was today just not your day?

272
00:31:36,604 --> 00:31:38,647
I am actually a beer drinker.

273
00:31:38,731 --> 00:31:42,109
But with all that's happening,
I think this is what I need.

274
00:31:45,904 --> 00:31:48,949
I don't think Ted Ignacio
is telling the truth.

275
00:31:49,742 --> 00:31:51,327
Someone ordered him…

276
00:31:52,620 --> 00:31:53,746
to confess.

277
00:31:54,830 --> 00:31:55,956
I already talked to him.

278
00:31:56,874 --> 00:31:59,293
Still nothing.
He's keeping his mouth shut.

279
00:32:00,419 --> 00:32:01,712
That bastard.

280
00:32:04,131 --> 00:32:07,926
At first, I really thought
it was a suicide.

281
00:32:09,511 --> 00:32:10,929
But you're right.

282
00:32:12,348 --> 00:32:14,183
There are details that don't match.

283
00:32:21,023 --> 00:32:22,107
So, Kyle…

284
00:32:23,317 --> 00:32:25,778
how was your first day at the university?

285
00:32:28,072 --> 00:32:29,531
I'm still adjusting.

286
00:32:30,616 --> 00:32:33,452
It's a good thing Pia and I
became project partners.

287
00:32:34,620 --> 00:32:36,121
I have a friend now.

288
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:42,920
That's your project?

289
00:32:44,630 --> 00:32:46,590
Pia can make that herself.

290
00:32:47,716 --> 00:32:50,427
Yeah, Pia can do that.

291
00:32:50,511 --> 00:32:53,389
Your sister's great, but…

292
00:32:54,515 --> 00:32:56,934
it's still better to have someone help.

293
00:32:57,017 --> 00:32:58,102
The output becomes better.

294
00:32:59,895 --> 00:33:01,480
That's why we're partners.

295
00:33:04,650 --> 00:33:07,361
Pia told me you weren't
answering her yesterday.

296
00:33:08,862 --> 00:33:10,030
I was just busy.

297
00:33:11,281 --> 00:33:12,324
I'm sorry again.

298
00:33:14,243 --> 00:33:15,411
It's okay.

299
00:33:24,044 --> 00:33:26,463
Is Matteo upset with Kyle?

300
00:33:29,800 --> 00:33:36,306
Your brother is just getting
to know your friend more.

301
00:33:37,015 --> 00:33:38,851
But he looks upset.

302
00:33:40,060 --> 00:33:42,896
I'm not upset.

303
00:33:42,980 --> 00:33:46,400
Don't worry.

304
00:33:53,407 --> 00:33:56,160
Are you okay?

305
00:33:59,413 --> 00:34:00,831
He's asking if you're okay.

306
00:34:07,421 --> 00:34:09,590
Eli rarely talks with others.

307
00:34:10,758 --> 00:34:12,092
But he's comfortable with you.

308
00:34:13,927 --> 00:34:17,055
Maybe we have the same vibe.

309
00:34:17,139 --> 00:34:18,891
We both lost a loved one.

310
00:34:20,851 --> 00:34:22,478
What do you mean?

311
00:34:25,856 --> 00:34:28,567
I heard during the wake of Teacher Sam…

312
00:34:29,485 --> 00:34:31,487
that Eli was close to her.

313
00:34:31,570 --> 00:34:34,114
Well, I'm also close with my mom.

314
00:34:34,198 --> 00:34:35,449
But she's gone.

315
00:34:38,202 --> 00:34:41,371
To be honest, this is my first
home-cooked meal in a while.

316
00:34:44,374 --> 00:34:45,918
What about your dad?

317
00:34:47,377 --> 00:34:48,796
He's always busy with work.

318
00:34:48,879 --> 00:34:51,089
Especially now that he's been promoted.

319
00:34:51,173 --> 00:34:53,383
Kyle, who's your father?

320
00:34:53,926 --> 00:34:55,469
He's Manu Cortez.

321
00:34:55,552 --> 00:34:57,805
The new chief of police.

322
00:35:57,030 --> 00:35:59,658
Dude, when will you be able
to make a deposit?

323
00:35:59,741 --> 00:36:02,327
There are already other people
inquiring about the unit.

324
00:36:02,411 --> 00:36:06,164
If you haven't signed a contract yet,
they might rent it to others.

325
00:36:33,191 --> 00:36:35,694
Dude, put the unit on hold.

326
00:36:36,278 --> 00:36:37,779
Reserve it for me for now.

327
00:36:37,863 --> 00:36:40,824
Dude, it's been reserved
for you for a long time.

328
00:36:40,908 --> 00:36:43,994
But my mom needs
the deposit for it already.

329
00:36:44,077 --> 00:36:46,038
They're already selling it for cheap.

330
00:36:46,121 --> 00:36:48,206
Can't we ask your mom for more time?

331
00:36:48,290 --> 00:36:50,375
I'm already doing my best to pay.

332
00:36:50,459 --> 00:36:51,418
I beg you.

333
00:36:51,501 --> 00:36:54,046
Alright, I'll try to talk to them.

334
00:36:54,129 --> 00:36:55,589
They might give in.

335
00:36:56,548 --> 00:36:57,758
Thank you.

336
00:36:57,841 --> 00:37:00,385
I promise I'll send the money
once I have it.

337
00:37:37,589 --> 00:37:39,633
Thanks for the dinner.
Let's have one again.

338
00:37:41,718 --> 00:37:43,804
Is that Kyle?

339
00:37:53,563 --> 00:37:58,902
Can we hang out with him again?

340
00:38:04,449 --> 00:38:05,742
Okay?

341
00:38:06,743 --> 00:38:09,621
Alright, then. You need to rest.

342
00:39:09,056 --> 00:39:10,932
I didn't expect that…

343
00:39:12,392 --> 00:39:14,227
Cortez is Kyle's father.

344
00:39:15,062 --> 00:39:17,064
But he's okay, he's nice.

345
00:39:17,147 --> 00:39:19,316
Unlike his father.

346
00:39:19,399 --> 00:39:22,152
It doesn't matter who his father is.

347
00:39:22,235 --> 00:39:25,739
As long as he gets along well
with the kids,

348
00:39:25,822 --> 00:39:28,033
especially with Eli,

349
00:39:28,742 --> 00:39:30,285
he's welcome here.

350
00:39:32,537 --> 00:39:33,747
You're right.

351
00:39:34,372 --> 00:39:36,208
I've never seen Eli like that before.

352
00:39:37,375 --> 00:39:39,503
Hopefully, it will continue.

353
00:39:40,962 --> 00:39:43,381
I want Eli to go back to the way he was.

354
00:39:43,465 --> 00:39:45,509
Cheerful.

355
00:39:45,592 --> 00:39:46,802
Jolly.

356
00:39:47,761 --> 00:39:48,887
I hope so.

357
00:39:50,097 --> 00:39:54,017
I hope that our weekend trip
will be helpful.

358
00:39:54,101 --> 00:39:56,103
I already arranged everything.

359
00:39:56,186 --> 00:39:58,772
I really hope that everything
will be alright, Anton.

360
00:39:59,439 --> 00:40:03,693
Because I want the kids
to see and feel that they are safe.

361
00:40:04,361 --> 00:40:06,905
That we can go back to the way it was.

362
00:40:22,963 --> 00:40:24,798
Let's meet tonight. Prepare the money.

363
00:40:24,881 --> 00:40:26,007
Wait for my instructions.

364
00:40:26,091 --> 00:40:27,968
Leave the money at the bell tower
of Escondido Parish at 10 p.m. sharp.

365
00:40:28,051 --> 00:40:29,136
Text me when you're done.

366
00:40:37,644 --> 00:40:40,480
Jackie. I'll just head out for a bit.

367
00:42:06,983 --> 00:42:09,277
You're not following instructions.

368
00:42:09,361 --> 00:42:11,321
I told you to text me, didn't I?

369
00:42:15,909 --> 00:42:17,827
I already left the money.

370
00:42:22,207 --> 00:42:26,503
Leave. Once we get the money,
I'll tell you where Sam's phone is.

371
00:42:37,931 --> 00:42:40,350
How can I make sure you won't betray me?

372
00:42:45,397 --> 00:42:48,149
You have no choice but to believe me.

373
00:43:15,385 --> 00:43:18,096
-Has he been asleep for a while?
-Yes, Ma.

374
00:43:18,972 --> 00:43:21,599
Ma, I want to show you something.

375
00:43:27,272 --> 00:43:29,524
Ma, take a look at Eli's drawings.

376
00:43:30,608 --> 00:43:32,110
They seem strange.

377
00:46:46,679 --> 00:46:48,973
Mama has a small request.

378
00:46:49,057 --> 00:46:52,810
No cell phone use while we're here.

379
00:46:55,772 --> 00:46:59,275
-Thank you for this trip.
-You're welcome.

380
00:46:59,359 --> 00:47:02,320
That's right. Let's focus on family first.

381
00:47:02,403 --> 00:47:04,364
Here feels happier.

382
00:47:04,447 --> 00:47:05,615
Can I ask you something
about your butterfly drawings?

383
00:47:07,158 --> 00:47:08,910
Every time I look at Eli,

384
00:47:08,993 --> 00:47:12,288
all I think is how he's the one
who paid for your sins.

385
00:47:12,372 --> 00:47:15,208
Didn't I choose to still be your wife

386
00:47:15,291 --> 00:47:17,585
even when I've stopped
loving you a long time ago?

387
00:47:17,669 --> 00:47:19,796
Ma, Eli is missing!

388
00:47:19,879 --> 00:47:22,632
I won't be able to forgive myself
if something happens to Eli.
